Package: SEMMS
Type: Package
Title: Variable Selection in Generalized Linear Models via Empirical Bayes
Version: 0.4.1
Authors@R: c(
    person("Haim", "Bar", email = "haim.bar@uconn.edu",
           role = c("aut", "cre")))
Author: Haim Bar
Maintainer: Haim Bar <haim.bar@uconn.edu>
Imports: Rcpp (>= 1.0.5), lme4
LinkingTo: Rcpp, RcppArmadillo
Depends: R (>= 3.6.0), car, MASS, edgefinder
Remotes: haimbar/edgefinder
Suggests: knitr, rmarkdown
VignetteBuilder: knitr
Description: Fits a three-component normal mixture model to the coefficients
    in the linear predictor of a GLM (Gaussian, Poisson, or binomial response)
    using an empirical Bayes approach and a Generalized Alternating Maximization
    algorithm. Version 0.4.1 extends fitSEMMSmixed() to Poisson and binomial
    responses using the proper IRLS (Penalised Quasi-Likelihood) working
    response (Breslow and Clayton, 1993), in addition to the Gaussian
    mixed-effects support introduced in version 0.4.0.
